<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-721-914  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 721 914.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 7 1990 v4 n27 p33(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Drive reads WORM, erasable media. (Optical Access InternationalInc.'s Access 650MF optical disk drive) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Optical Access International Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Optical Access International Access 650MF (Removable hard diskdrive) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionOptical DisksDisk DrivesSmall Computer Systems Interface.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Henry NorrandM;Woburn, Mass.andP;  -- Optical Access International Inc. will this week unveilwhat it called &quot;the world's first multifunction optical storage system forMacintosh,&quot; a drive that can read from and write to both WORM and erasableoptical discs.andM;Based on a new dual-mode technology introduced in June by PioneerCommunications of America Inc. (see MacWEEK, June 5), the Access 650MFincorporates a 5.25-inch mechanism from Laser Magnetic Storage InternationalCo.andP;  The drive switches transparently between WORM (write-once-read-many) anderasable modes, automatically recognizing what type of media is inserted.andM;The drive, which uses 654-Mbyte dual-sided cartridges in a new sampled servoformat, features an average access time of 53 milliseconds and a sustainedtransfer rate of 491 Kbytes per second.andP;  It can read existing WORM cartridgesused in Laser Magnetic Storage International LD-510 drivesbut cannot readfrom or write to the cartridges used in other erasable optical systems on themarket.andM;Available now, the Optical Access International SCSI drive carries a listprice of $4,995, but the company said it is offering a special promotionalprice of $3,295 on orders received before Sept.andP;  15.andM;The drive has a 256-Kbyte hardware buffer to improve performance.andP;  In WORMmode, the company said, the drive maximizes disk space by sequentiallywriting to only the changed blocks as files are updated.andM;Optical Access International will offer WORM cartridges at $125 and erasableones at $250 for the new drive.andP;  Aside from a floppy disk containing thecompany's device driver, no media are shipped with the drive.andM;Optical Access International Inc. is located at 36 Commerce Way, Woburn,Mass.andP;  01801; (617) 935-2679; (800) 523-2679.andO;</TEXT></DOC>